<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/412789-anastasia">Anastasia</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It comes from the work of an author Ambrose liked, Jacob Boehme. From page 229: Boehme believed &quot;God had hidden clues for humanity&apos;s betterment inside<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It comes from the work of an author Ambrose liked, Jacob Boehme. From page 229: Boehme believed "God had hidden clues for humanity's betterment inside the design of every flower, leaf, fruit and tree on earth. All the natural world was a divine code, Boehme claimed, containing proof of our Creator's love." Ambrose briefly lost his mind in college after reading Boehme, remember?<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
