  <span id="freeText10464044464143794160" style="display:none">So many thoughts, so little time - so....<br /><br />Elizabeth Gilbert, author of that turnip of a book – <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/19501.Eat__Pray__Love" title="Eat, Pray, Love by Elizabeth Gilbert" rel="nofollow noopener">Eat, Pray, Love</a>, has written <b>an absolute peach</b> of a big, sprawling novel in <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17465453.The_Signature_of_All_Things" title="The Signature of All Things by Elizabeth Gilbert" rel="nofollow noopener">The Signature of All Things</a>. <br /><br /><b>Luscious, ambitious, lyrical, satisfying</b>; nothing in this novel will fail to keep you spellbound. I could wax lyrically all day about this book. <br /><br />Thank-you to Sally Howes for recommending this to me. Most Highly Recommended. 5★</span>
