<span id="freeTextContainer16626679967574938218">I started out enjoying this book very much and I was glad because I had been avoiding reading it for a while due to the fact that I disliked <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/19501.Eat__Pray__Love' title='Eat, Pray, Love by Elizabeth Gilbert' rel='nofollow noopener'>Eat, Pray, Love</a> so much.<a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17465453.The_Signature_of_All_Things' title='The Signature of All Things by Elizabeth Gilbert' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Signature of All Things</a> is a very different kind of book however and it is mostly interesting, well,written and populated with intriguing characters. Sadly though it is too long and the last section just meanders along without direction. Which is a great shame because I was left thinking it was just an okay book when in fact a la</span>
